would you be willing to run Sprq Point
for the next six months?

14:31.083 --> 14:33.622
Eighteen if they find the hard drive
in my sister's basement.

14:33.647 --> 14:36.492
Wow. Um... I...

14:36.780 --> 14:40.102
Wait, so you want me to take
over the entire company?

14:40.126 --> 14:41.803
No, I admit there's gonna
be a lot of press on this,

14:41.827 --> 14:43.772
and the job won't be easy.

14:43.796 --> 14:46.474
There's a board meeting
in Singapore on Friday

14:46.499 --> 14:48.710
and I need you to
come with for approval.

14:48.734 --> 14:50.179
What do you say?

14:50.636 --> 14:52.630
I mean, it's gonna be
a very complicated deal.

14:52.655 --> 14:55.057
I'm gonna have to talk to
my lawyer... of course!

15:03.973 --> 15:06.873
Before you say anything,
let me get this out.

15:08.978 --> 15:11.766
The reason why I broke
up with you is because

15:12.112 --> 15:13.656
I'm afraid.

15:13.681 --> 15:16.152
I'm afraid of opening up to you

15:16.177 --> 15:18.112
and telling you how I really feel.

15:20.034 --> 15:23.690
I haven't always been on
the receiving side of love,

15:24.064 --> 15:26.459
and it makes me feel like
I have to protect myself

15:26.483 --> 15:30.063
and I push people away and
nobody should live like that.

15:30.510 --> 15:32.664
So I want to say before it's too late

15:32.689 --> 15:35.768
that I really care about you,

15:36.306 --> 15:39.572
and I'm willing to make this
work come hell or high water.

15:40.228 --> 15:42.720
That was a cruise ship joke.

15:44.291 --> 15:45.401
Are you not responding because

15:45.425 --> 15:46.569
you don't want to get back together

15:46.593 --> 15:48.137
or because you don't like my comedy?

15:48.161 --> 15:50.135
Either way it's perfectly...

15:54.821 --> 15:57.721
Okay, sailor. Aye, aye.

16:01.752 --> 16:03.563
So hey, what are you in the mood for?

16:03.588 --> 16:06.945
I think we could do a marathon
of Orson Welles films,

16:06.970 --> 16:09.633
or "Sausage Party."
I could go either way.

16:09.658 --> 16:12.931
You pick, but before we get into that...

16:13.627 --> 16:15.098
I need to tell you something.

16:15.775 --> 16:17.953
I got your job back today.

16:17.978 --> 16:19.844
What? How?

16:19.869 --> 16:21.563
I talked to Danny Michael Davis,

16:21.588 --> 16:23.032
and I convinced him.

16:23.056 --> 16:24.955
- You did?
- Sure did.

16:24.980 --> 16:28.517
So, today isn't so bad after all.

16:28.542 --> 16:31.525
It's actually turning out
to be pretty darn good.

16:31.550 --> 16:35.955
Yeah, that's... incredible.
Um, it's just...

16:37.342 --> 16:39.486
I don't want the job back.

16:40.060 --> 16:41.453
Why not?

16:41.478 --> 16:43.619
Well, look, I really appreciate it,

16:43.643 --> 16:45.355
but I liked the way it felt

16:45.379 --> 16:47.524
being in charge on the 6th floor.

16:47.549 --> 16:50.308
It made me feel good,
and I was good at it.

16:50.978 --> 16:53.519
I just don't want to go backwards, Zoey.

16:53.544 --> 16:55.784
I was actually walking
around North Beach today

16:55.809 --> 16:57.972
just thinking, and I realized that

16:57.997 --> 17:00.105
I'm excited about the future, you know?

17:00.130 --> 17:03.925
Diving into the unknown,
trying something new.

17:03.950 --> 17:06.580
It might be scary, but... Are you mad?

17:06.606 --> 17:10.152
No. I...

17:10.309 --> 17:13.002
like seeing this side of you.

17:13.028 --> 17:15.839
Oh, cool. Well, yeah,
I just feel like life is short,

17:15.864 --> 17:17.377
and I'm not sure what...

17:22.057 --> 17:23.869
Why'd you do that?

17:24.823 --> 17:27.220
'Cause I felt like it.

17:30.193 --> 17:31.964
You feel like this?

17:41.952 --> 17:45.542
♪ What would I do without
your smart mouth ♪

17:45.567 --> 17:49.280
♪ Drawing me in,
and you kicking me out ♪

17:49.305 --> 17:54.175
♪ Got my head spinning, no kidding ♪

17:54.200 --> 17:57.073
♪ I can't pin you down ♪

17:57.098 --> 18:00.837
♪ What's going on in
that beautiful mind ♪

18:00.862 --> 18:04.808
♪ I'm on your magical mystery ride ♪

18:04.833 --> 18:07.480
♪ And I'm so dizzy ♪

18:07.505 --> 18:09.383
♪ Don't know what hit me ♪

18:09.408 --> 18:12.954
♪ But I'll be all right ♪

18:12.979 --> 18:16.525
♪ My head's underwater ♪

18:16.550 --> 18:20.636
♪ But I'm breathing fine ♪

18:20.661 --> 18:25.737
♪ You're crazy and I'm out of my mind ♪

18:26.351 --> 18:29.612
♪ 'Cause all of me ♪

18:35.108 --> 18:36.919
You don't know this,

18:36.944 --> 18:41.471
but you're singing another
love song to me right now.

18:41.496 --> 18:43.607
What? So embarrassing.

18:43.632 --> 18:46.127
Oh, no, it's fine. It's just,
could you...

18:46.152 --> 18:48.713
- Think about something else?
- Just now, for...

18:48.737 --> 18:50.470
Like something sexier, dirtier?

18:50.495 --> 18:51.520
- I mean, sure.
- Is that the kind of vibe...

18:51.544 --> 18:52.750
If you could do that,
that would be great.

18:52.774 --> 18:54.752
Yeah, I could do that.
It's already done.

18:54.776 --> 18:56.009
Come here.

18:58.769 --> 19:00.591
♪ One, two, three, four ♪

19:00.615 --> 19:01.978
♪ Uno, do', tres ♪

19:02.003 --> 19:03.661
♪ I know you want me ♪

19:03.685 --> 19:05.530
♪ You know I want cha ♪

19:05.554 --> 19:07.431
♪ I know you want me ♪

19:07.455 --> 19:09.333
♪ You know I want cha ♪

19:09.357 --> 19:11.314
♪ I know you want me, ah ♪

19:11.339 --> 19:13.150
♪ You know I want cha, ha ♪

19:13.175 --> 19:14.886
♪ I know you... ♪

19:15.027 --> 19:17.198
I'm sorry, but, um...

19:17.699 --> 19:20.158
- Ow.
- Changed my mind.

19:20.183 --> 19:22.142
Okay? Take it back.

19:22.167 --> 19:25.190
Um... how about you just
make your mind go blank?

19:25.215 --> 19:26.893
Like, don't think about anything.

19:26.917 --> 19:28.383
Okay.

19:32.822 --> 19:34.366
Come here.

19:37.316 --> 19:39.038
Don't get that, please.

19:39.062 --> 19:40.573
Oh...

19:41.612 --> 19:42.970
I just have to check,

19:42.995 --> 19:45.600
and I'll only answer it if it's, um...

19:49.769 --> 19:52.919
Hello? Hi, Howie.

19:53.456 --> 19:55.268
No, yeah.

19:55.503 --> 19:57.135
I'll be right there.

19:59.745 --> 20:01.316
What was that?

20:01.577 --> 20:03.277
The bad moon.

20:04.716 --> 20:06.483
It rose.

20:13.752 --> 20:14.877
Zoey.

20:14.902 --> 20:17.370
Can you come in the kitchen
for a moment, please?

20:18.847 --> 20:21.808
Uh, can you just give me, um, a minute?

20:21.833 --> 20:22.966
Sure.

20:25.363 --> 20:27.205
Over the past couple weeks,

20:27.230 --> 20:30.142
Mitch has been decreasing
his food and fluid intake

20:30.166 --> 20:31.322
by the day.

20:31.347 --> 20:34.362
He has now completely lost
the ability to swallow.

20:34.614 --> 20:36.394
In a matter of hours,

20:36.419 --> 20:38.808
his organs will shut down.

20:39.840 --> 20:42.566
I have a steady supply of morphine

20:42.591 --> 20:44.391
to keep him comfortable.

20:45.681 --> 20:49.961
I know, as much as you
have prepared for this moment,

20:49.986 --> 20:52.237
you can only prepare so much.

20:52.262 --> 20:56.142
But I'm here,
and will do everything I can,

20:56.167 --> 20:58.894
to help ease this transition
for everyone.

20:58.919 --> 21:00.962
I just can't believe
he's not even gonna get

21:00.987 --> 21:03.667
to meet his grandson, you know?

21:03.692 --> 21:07.094
I don't... I feel really...
I gotta go lie down.

21:07.969 --> 21:10.025
Emily, why don't you go
and sit with him?

21:10.050 --> 21:12.261
And I'll be in in a minute.

21:32.131 --> 21:36.105
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Simon, hey. It's Max.

21:36.799 --> 21:39.478
Zoey's dad isn't doing well, and...

21:39.502 --> 21:41.969
<i>I think she wanted you to know that.</i>

21:43.992 --> 21:46.269
Can I do anything?

21:46.980 --> 21:49.120
Uh, maybe just shoot her a text,

21:49.145 --> 21:52.347
or whatever you guys do and...

21:52.636 --> 21:54.042
Whenever you can.

21:54.536 --> 21:56.831
Hey, Max, um...

21:57.554 --> 21:59.339
Thanks for calling.

21:59.722 --> 22:01.425
I appreciate it.

22:03.475 --> 22:05.209
Yeah.

22:06.008 --> 22:08.942
David, do you want to go talk to him?

22:10.448 --> 22:13.284
I do. Uh... I mean...

22:13.309 --> 22:15.713
I have so much I want to ask
him and say to him still,

22:15.738 --> 22:18.198
but I don't... I don't want
him to see me like this.

22:18.223 --> 22:20.425
He never held back his emotions.

22:20.450 --> 22:21.983
You shouldn't either.

22:24.181 --> 22:26.824
Since when did you turn
into our spiritual guru?

22:26.849 --> 22:30.084
Ever since a magical MRI
machine changed me forever.

22:34.361 --> 22:36.568
Should I stay in here, or...

22:36.593 --> 22:41.355
No, no. You're my wife,
and he loves you.

22:41.380 --> 22:43.146
He'd want to say goodbye.

22:51.871 --> 22:54.167
Oh, wait. I want to say goodbye to you.

22:55.855 --> 22:58.386
- I'm so sorry, Maggie.
- I know.

22:58.708 --> 23:01.941
I'm so glad you were here.
Did you get a chance to...

23:01.966 --> 23:04.099
Yeah, I did, I did.

23:05.644 --> 23:07.769
And, uh...

23:07.910 --> 23:11.042
I let him know exactly
how I feel about his daughter.

23:13.020 --> 23:15.300
I'm pretty sure he already knows.

23:26.262 --> 23:32.222
♪ Goodnight, my angel,
time to close your eyes ♪

23:32.485 --> 23:38.237
♪ And save these questions
for another day ♪

23:38.680 --> 23:44.378
♪ I think I know what
you've been asking me ♪

23:44.802 --> 23:50.816
♪ I think you know what
I've been trying to say ♪

23:51.034 --> 23:56.925
♪ I promised I would never leave you ♪

23:57.400 --> 24:01.667
♪ And you should always know ♪

24:03.783 --> 24:09.783
♪ Wherever you may go,
no matter where you are ♪

24:09.948 --> 24:15.894
♪ I never will be far away ♪

24:16.099 --> 24:21.566
♪ Goodnight, my angel,
now it's time to sleep ♪

24:22.030 --> 24:27.878
♪ And still so many
things I want to say ♪

24:28.389 --> 24:34.120
♪ Remember all the
songs you sang for me ♪

24:34.606 --> 24:40.402
♪ When we went sailing
on an emerald bay ♪

24:40.896 --> 24:46.589
♪ And like a boat out on the ocean ♪

24:47.165 --> 24:50.967
♪ I'm rocking you to sleep ♪

24:53.566 --> 24:59.566
♪ The water's dark and deep,
inside this ancient heart ♪

24:59.838 --> 25:05.709
♪ You'll always be a part of me ♪

25:08.910 --> 25:15.003
♪ Goodnight, my angel,
now it's time to dream ♪

25:15.370 --> 25:21.230
♪ And dream how wonderful
your life will be ♪

25:21.535 --> 25:27.535
♪ Someday your child may cry,
and if you sing this lullaby ♪

25:27.970 --> 25:30.547
♪ Then in your heart ♪

25:30.572 --> 25:34.845
♪ There will always be a part ♪

25:36.173 --> 25:39.345
♪ Of me ♪

25:54.064 --> 25:55.509
So.

25:55.534 --> 25:57.486
Listen, about earlier...

25:57.510 --> 26:00.360
Look, we will have
plenty of time to talk about,

26:00.385 --> 26:02.493
dissect, and analyze that

26:02.518 --> 26:04.689
which I'm sure we will do ad nauseum.

26:05.726 --> 26:07.157
Just...

26:08.392 --> 26:10.665
focus on yourself right now.

26:10.985 --> 26:12.368
Okay?

26:21.174 --> 26:23.642
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

26:36.795 --> 26:38.861
You weren't supposed to see me.

26:39.923 --> 26:42.765
I was just gonna drop off
this lasagna that I made.

26:42.790 --> 26:45.437
- You made lasagna?
- Yeah. I just remembered

26:45.462 --> 26:48.142
a lot of people brought
over casseroles for us.

26:48.563 --> 26:50.423
Seemed like the thing to do.

26:51.913 --> 26:54.197
Hey, I'm... I'm so sorry.

26:54.222 --> 26:55.875
I'm gonna let you get back in there.

26:55.900 --> 26:59.020
Just know that I know.

26:59.462 --> 27:02.756
And I'm here, whenever you need me.

27:04.103 --> 27:05.290
You helped me and I'm...

27:05.315 --> 27:07.587
I'm more than ready to return the favor.

27:09.079 --> 27:10.962
Do you still have that
grief basket I gave you?

27:10.987 --> 27:12.131
I might need it.

27:12.156 --> 27:13.892
Oh, you're gonna get your very own.

27:13.917 --> 27:15.259
Maybe a grief duffle.

27:15.284 --> 27:16.868
Or a trunk.

27:17.377 --> 27:19.400
I go big or go home.

27:25.861 --> 27:28.353
I'm just gonna go upstairs
and rest for a little bit.

27:28.378 --> 27:30.679
- Is that okay?
- Of course, yeah.

27:33.133 --> 27:35.025
Is it weird if I eat something?

27:41.895 --> 27:45.103
What is... is that lasagna?

27:46.741 --> 27:48.728
Yeah, Howie and I moved him.

27:48.753 --> 27:51.632
Just thought he'd be
more comfortable in bed.

27:58.284 --> 28:02.962
♪ Stars shining bright above you ♪

28:03.781 --> 28:09.207
♪ Night breezes seem to whisper
"I love you" ♪

28:09.637 --> 28:14.652
♪ Birds singing in the sycamore tree ♪

28:14.896 --> 28:19.231
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

28:20.935 --> 28:25.738
♪ Say "Nighty night" and kiss me ♪

28:26.540 --> 28:32.082
♪ Just hold me tight and
tell me you'll miss me ♪

28:32.504 --> 28:37.519
♪ While I'm alone and blue as can be ♪

28:37.849 --> 28:41.884
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

28:44.519 --> 28:49.597
♪ In your dreams, whatever they be ♪

28:49.715 --> 28:55.715
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

29:07.661 --> 29:12.097
Is this when we have the talk
about what death is like?

29:13.399 --> 29:15.004
Depends.

29:16.080 --> 29:19.599
Are you looking for some
deep insights from me,

29:19.624 --> 29:21.676
some words of wisdom?

29:23.185 --> 29:25.504
I'm game if you got 'em.

29:27.899 --> 29:32.580
Death is hideous,
and ugly, and grotesque,

29:32.604 --> 29:36.806
and wildly, wildly unfair.

29:38.636 --> 29:40.420
Or, maybe...

29:40.445 --> 29:44.510
death is beautiful, and spiritual,

29:44.535 --> 29:48.429
and transcendent,
and sometimes a very necessary

29:48.453 --> 29:51.705
and very freeing escape
from our physical bodies

29:51.730 --> 29:54.933
when they are no longer habitable.

29:56.301 --> 29:58.869
Which way do you think I
should choose to look at it?

30:01.488 --> 30:04.682
Zoey, if you'd like to go
talk to your dad,

30:04.707 --> 30:07.527
I think now would be a good time.

30:13.902 --> 30:15.698
Hey, Dad.

30:19.681 --> 30:24.117
I'm going to try to go
another way with this tonight.

30:31.581 --> 30:34.107
I'm doing pretty well at work.

30:35.105 --> 30:37.361
Uh, that guy that I liked

30:37.386 --> 30:40.180
who was engaged now likes me.

30:40.902 --> 30:44.011
Although I did just hook up
with my best friend, so...

30:44.761 --> 30:46.832
that complicates things.

30:49.402 --> 30:52.721
Oh, and those big musical
numbers I've been hearing?

30:52.746 --> 30:54.979
This might be totally crazy, but

30:55.004 --> 31:00.011
I'm not sure I'm minding them...

31:00.465 --> 31:02.160
like I used to.

31:03.004 --> 31:06.097
I think that they might
actually be helping me.

31:07.735 --> 31:09.601
Believe me, I'm not...

31:12.629 --> 31:14.668
doing well, but...

31:16.285 --> 31:18.754
I'm not doing that badly, either.

31:19.301 --> 31:22.330
Thought maybe you'd want to hear that,

31:22.355 --> 31:24.340
that your daughter's okay.

31:25.254 --> 31:27.654
You know, in case
you were worried or anything.

31:30.371 --> 31:31.912
Howie?

31:32.317 --> 31:35.100
- What's happening right now?
- David?

31:35.462 --> 31:37.975
His lungs are...

31:38.000 --> 31:40.311
Let me give him some more morphine.

31:40.926 --> 31:43.733
- This is normal?
- Yes.

32:04.759 --> 32:06.637
I love you so much.

32:06.662 --> 32:08.474
It's okay. It's gonna be okay.

32:08.499 --> 32:11.061
- You doing okay?
- You are so loved.

32:11.590 --> 32:13.989
I love you, my darling.

32:16.018 --> 32:18.295
I love you so much.

32:18.710 --> 32:20.795
You'll be okay.

32:22.707 --> 32:24.428
- Psst!
- ... so much.

32:24.453 --> 32:25.953
Over here!

32:27.168 --> 32:29.401
I want to talk to you for a minute.

32:33.154 --> 32:35.186
Come on!

32:52.863 --> 32:54.936
Dance with me.

33:10.013 --> 33:12.224
I don't hear any music.

33:12.249 --> 33:14.115
Sure you do, Zoey.

33:15.546 --> 33:17.029
What do you call those songs

33:17.054 --> 33:19.154
that other people keep singing to you?

33:20.579 --> 33:22.608
Heart songs.

33:24.025 --> 33:26.295
Well, that's a good name for them.

33:30.848 --> 33:33.623
But what do I do when
I can't hear you sing anymore?

33:33.648 --> 33:36.394
Oh, you're always gonna hear me,

33:36.666 --> 33:38.910
whether it's a song or not.

33:39.348 --> 33:43.670
All you have to do is... listen.

33:45.194 --> 33:48.537
Oh, what are you looking over there for?

33:51.790 --> 33:53.772
I'm right here.

34:06.528 --> 34:08.161
Now...

34:09.812 --> 34:14.420
I know we can do better than this.

35:09.465 --> 35:11.122
Shall we do this?

35:13.145 --> 35:16.106
We can stay in the car a few
more minutes if you want, Mom.

35:16.639 --> 35:18.269
Yeah, we don't mind.

35:18.505 --> 35:21.387
I actually prefer this
to being around people.

35:23.993 --> 35:25.762
No.

35:28.338 --> 35:30.074
It's okay. I mean, I guess we've gotta

35:30.099 --> 35:32.512
face the music sometime, right?

35:59.991 --> 36:03.590
♪ A long, long time ago ♪

36:03.615 --> 36:06.457
♪ I can still remember ♪

36:06.482 --> 36:11.730
♪ How the music used to make me smile ♪

36:11.755 --> 36:15.629
♪ And I knew if I had my chance ♪

36:15.654 --> 36:18.816
♪ That I could make those people dance ♪

36:18.841 --> 36:24.245
♪ And maybe they'd be
happy for a while ♪

36:25.221 --> 36:28.668
♪ But February made me shiver ♪

36:28.693 --> 36:32.172
♪ With every paper I'd deliver ♪

36:32.665 --> 36:35.894
♪ Bad news on the doorstep ♪

36:36.144 --> 36:39.545
♪ I couldn't take one more step ♪

36:40.557 --> 36:44.590
♪ I can't remember if I cried ♪

36:44.615 --> 36:48.595
♪ When I read about his widowed bride ♪

36:48.620 --> 36:53.101
♪ But something touched me deep inside ♪

36:53.251 --> 37:00.251
♪ The day the music died ♪

37:01.768 --> 37:06.394
♪ So bye, bye Miss American Pie ♪

37:06.419 --> 37:11.738
♪ Drove my Chevy to the
levee but the levee was dry ♪

37:11.763 --> 37:16.480
♪ And them good ole boys were
drinking whiskey and rye ♪

37:16.505 --> 37:21.508
♪ Singin' this'll be
the day that I die ♪

37:22.165 --> 37:27.117
♪ This'll be the day that I die ♪

37:28.955 --> 37:31.406
♪ Did you write the book of love ♪

37:31.431 --> 37:35.414
♪ And do you have faith in God above ♪

37:35.807 --> 37:39.531
♪ If the Bible tells you so? ♪

37:39.556 --> 37:43.436
♪ Oh, do you believe in rock and roll? ♪

37:43.461 --> 37:47.484
♪ Can music save your mortal soul? ♪

37:47.509 --> 37:53.625
♪ And can you teach me
how to dance real slow? ♪

37:53.650 --> 37:57.008
♪ Well, I know that
you're in love with him ♪

37:57.033 --> 38:00.648
♪ 'Cause I saw you dancin' in the gym ♪

38:00.673 --> 38:03.883
♪ You both kicked off your shoes ♪

38:03.908 --> 38:07.148
♪ Man, I dig those rhythm and blues ♪

38:07.173 --> 38:11.007
♪ Whoo, I was a lonely
teenage broncin' buck ♪

38:11.032 --> 38:14.545
♪ With a pink carnation
and a pickup truck ♪

38:14.570 --> 38:18.116
♪ But I knew I was out of luck ♪

38:18.141 --> 38:23.273
♪ The day the music died ♪

38:23.783 --> 38:25.046
♪ I started singing ♪

38:25.071 --> 38:28.050
♪ Bye, bye Miss American Pie ♪

38:28.075 --> 38:31.609
♪ Drove my Chevy to the
levee but the levee was dry ♪

38:31.634 --> 38:34.859
♪ Them good ole boys were
drinking whiskey and rye ♪

